Osun State is planning to host an international marathon race for about 10,000 athletes across the world on May 2. At a press conference in Osogbo, the Commissioner for Women, Children and Social Affairs, Olubukola Olaboopo, said the race tagged “Osun Women Run 2020” the state government is organising the event in collaboration with the Association of International Marathons and Distance Race and Bran Dove International Ltd. She said the race would begin from the state secretariat and terminate at the Osogbo City Stadium. She described the event as a women rights marathon. According to her, the event which is being powered by her Ministry, will attract women participants from across the world, including the United Kingdom (UK), USA, South Africa, Rwanda, Kenya, Ethiopia among others. 